00:17:48,067 --> 00:17:50,667
sometimes you are braver when
you admit

270
00:17:50,733 --> 00:17:51,700
that you can't do it alone.

271
00:17:57,233 --> 00:17:58,100
We're done for today.

272
00:17:58,900 --> 00:18:02,500
Let's just make it up some other
day for your community service.

273
00:18:03,567 --> 00:18:08,167
So, you can wash your hands
and you can eat your vegetables.

274
00:18:14,067 --> 00:18:14,533
Okay.

275
00:18:15,400 --> 00:18:16,133
Let's go.

276
00:18:18,233 --> 00:18:18,967
You guys can follow us.

277
00:18:19,733 --> 00:18:20,467
Do you need help?

278
00:18:21,400 --> 00:18:22,233
Do you want something
to wrap it with?

279
00:18:24,433 --> 00:18:24,833
Oh, sorry.

280
00:18:47,233 --> 00:18:49,433
Oh God, it's been such
a long day.

281
00:18:59,400 --> 00:19:01,033
Is it a perfect time to
start a business now?

282
00:19:02,800 --> 00:19:05,733
Well, there is no perfect
time to start a business.

283
00:19:05,800 --> 00:19:08,400
You start a business because
you have a good idea

284
00:19:08,467 --> 00:19:11,200
which you honestly believe
that you can sell.

285
00:19:12,467 --> 00:19:15,067
If you wait for a perfect time
to start a business

286
00:19:15,133 --> 00:19:19,233
maybe the day after tomorrow
someone started that business

287
00:19:19,300 --> 00:19:20,600
while you are still
thinking about it.

288
00:19:21,733 --> 00:19:26,233
So, what's more important rather
than the perfect timing

289
00:19:26,300 --> 00:19:27,400
is you should be prepared.

290
00:19:28,667 --> 00:19:29,767
You should be ready.

291
00:19:31,000 --> 00:19:34,233
My advice is not to wait
for the perfect moment.

292
00:19:35,433 --> 00:19:37,367
Start your business now.

293
00:19:37,433 --> 00:19:39,133
You're the last person
I want to see,

294
00:19:40,100 --> 00:19:41,800
the face of my ex-husband.

295
00:20:16,800 --> 00:20:17,333
Tiff?

296
00:20:18,967 --> 00:20:22,333
Do you think I'm looking for
your Daddy in my boyfriends?

297
00:20:24,800 --> 00:20:25,900
Mom, to tell you honestly...

298
00:20:27,633 --> 00:20:28,133
yes.

299
00:20:30,467 --> 00:20:32,400
Okay Mom, so let's compare.

300
00:20:32,467 --> 00:20:33,600
I'm going to stalk you.

301
00:20:34,733 --> 00:20:36,600
Okay, your social media
accounts.

302
00:20:38,267 --> 00:20:38,567
Okay.

303
00:20:39,600 --> 00:20:44,833
So, this is Michael,
this is Rafa.

304
00:20:44,900 --> 00:20:49,867
This is Timothy,
and this is Richard.

305
00:20:49,933 --> 00:20:50,867
Oh, and Edward.

306
00:20:51,767 --> 00:20:53,233
So, back, back, back...

307
00:20:54,267 --> 00:20:57,567
exhibit A, exhibit b, exhibit c.

308
00:20:58,767 --> 00:20:59,433
What, Mom?

309
00:20:59,500 --> 00:21:00,500
Do you want me to continue?

310
00:21:00,567 --> 00:21:02,100
Because I have until x, y, z.

311
00:21:04,500 --> 00:21:05,300
See Mom?

312
00:21:06,667 --> 00:21:08,267
of all the people you've been
in a relationship with

313
00:21:08,367 --> 00:21:09,900
for the past few years,

314
00:21:09,967 --> 00:21:12,200
you're still looking for Dad
in all of them.

315
00:21:14,367 --> 00:21:17,500
And I'm not saying this to you
to ridicule you or something.

316
00:21:19,533 --> 00:21:21,533
But as your concerned daughter,

317
00:21:23,867 --> 00:21:26,767
your happiness is
very important to me.

318
00:21:46,100 --> 00:21:49,467
So how was the first day
of community service?

319
00:21:49,767 --> 00:21:50,400
It was nice.

320
00:21:51,600 --> 00:21:55,000
It's a bit hard but,
I felt good.

321
00:21:56,200 --> 00:21:57,267
What made you feel good?

322
00:22:05,867 --> 00:22:06,567
I'll press it.

323
00:22:07,933 --> 00:22:08,533
Sorry.

324
00:22:36,800 --> 00:22:38,700
Love, are you still there?

325
00:22:39,800 --> 00:22:40,667
Yes, Love.

326
00:22:42,133 --> 00:22:42,867
Yes.

327
00:22:45,300 --> 00:22:47,567
Yeah, I felt good.

328
00:22:48,600 --> 00:22:51,867
We actually, our activity was
all about you know...

329
00:22:53,933 --> 00:22:56,533
doing well for
mother nature and,

330
00:22:57,500 --> 00:23:01,433
it's difficult but it was,
it felt good.

331
00:23:02,500 --> 00:23:04,800
Maybe you're already tired,
I won't keep you up.

332
00:23:05,833 --> 00:23:07,100
You should rest.

333
00:23:07,167 --> 00:23:09,833
As soon as I find the time
I'll go there to Sorsogon.

334
00:23:10,333 --> 00:23:10,933
Okay, Love?

335
00:23:11,833 --> 00:23:12,767
Good night.

336
00:23:12,833 --> 00:23:14,500
Good night, good night.

337
00:24:08,367 --> 00:24:09,700
What is the rumor?

338
00:24:09,767 --> 00:24:13,467
It seems like it's hard
to get rid of the resentment

339
00:24:13,533 --> 00:24:14,700
that was kept for a long time.

340
00:24:14,767 --> 00:24:17,367
Didn't I tell you that I don't
want to hear anything about her?

341
00:24:17,433 --> 00:24:19,033
Why are you stubborn?

342
00:24:19,100 --> 00:24:20,800
I did a search
on your stepmother.

343
00:24:20,867 --> 00:24:23,033
I just found Sorsogon
and there she was.

344
00:24:23,100 --> 00:24:24,133
It's my community service.

345
00:24:24,200 --> 00:24:25,200
What will I do?

346
00:24:25,267 --> 00:24:27,133
Well, we will clean all
the mess.

347
00:24:27,200 --> 00:24:28,267
Who will clean this?

348
00:24:28,333 --> 00:24:29,533
You.

349
00:24:29,633 --> 00:24:33,200
He thinks he can get me with
his cute and charming ways.

350
00:24:33,267 --> 00:24:34,167
In his dreams.

351
00:24:34,233 --> 00:24:35,667
We're going to Sorsogon.

352
00:24:35,733 --> 00:24:37,333
Do you know that your
Auntie Celeste is there?

353
00:24:37,400 --> 00:24:39,500
This project has nothing
to do with her.

354
00:24:39,567 --> 00:24:42,333
It's just a coincidence
that we want to go there

355
00:24:42,400 --> 00:24:43,667
where she is making a mess.

356
00:24:43,733 --> 00:24:46,600
If she is very eager
to leave this house,

357
00:24:46,667 --> 00:24:50,600
as for me I can't wait for her
to get out of our lives.

358
00:25:05,433 --> 00:25:06,867
Why are you doing this?

359
00:25:06,933 --> 00:25:08,533
It's about Tonito.

360
00:25:08,600 --> 00:25:09,700
What about Tonito?

361
00:25:09,767 --> 00:25:11,033
I want him back.

362
00:25:11,100 --> 00:25:12,700
Sometimes you should
relax in your life.

363
00:25:12,767 --> 00:25:13,967
You know appreciate things.

364
00:25:14,933 --> 00:25:16,633
Appreciate the people
who are important to you.

365
00:25:17,267 --> 00:25:18,367
Yeah, very much.

366
00:25:18,433 --> 00:25:20,700
I appreciate all the people
who are important to me

367
00:25:20,767 --> 00:25:24,167
especially Tonito because Tonito
didn't leave me hanging.
